snippet: At 17, Lia Neal has become only the second African-American female swimmer to make it to the Olympics. Her parents were brought together by their own American dreams.
abstract: William C Rhoden Sports of The Times column profiles Lia Neal, who has become only the second African-American female swimmer to make the US Olympic team.
lead_paragraph: At 17, Lia Neal has become only the second African-American female swimmer to make it to the Olympics. Her parents were brought together by their own American dreams.

headline.seo: Olympic Swimmer Lia Neal Built Her Dream in Brooklyn
